<p style="text-align:justify;">finding a fair opening we took our departure.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Our party consisted of M<sup>r</sup> La Roque, M<sup>r</sup> La France, four Voyageurs and myself.  Four horses carried our assortment for trade and twice as many were assigned to carry ourselves &#8211; the whole in charge of M<sup>r</sup> La Roque, a deserving young Gentleman.  As for myself, happening to be newly arrived in the Indian Country, I was placed as an assistant to M<sup>r</sup> La <span class="DelHand-author">Roque</span> <span class="AddHand-author">France</span>, for he did not know how to write.  We proceeded, but to avoid the Natives we were obliged to lengthen our journey by taking a circuitous <span style="text-decoration:underline;">route</span>, which conducted us trough many extensive plains; most of which were in flames, as is generally the case at this season of the year.</p>
